# Template Learnings Rule

When working in an app repository that was created from this template:

- If you discover a reusable implementation pattern, document it in `docs/learnings/`.
- Keep learnings separate from execution tracking in tasks.
- Each learnings entry should include:
  - Problem
  - Reusable Pattern
  - Proposed Template Change
  - Risk and Rollout Notes
  - Backport Status
- Update `docs/learnings/catalog.json` when adding or modifying an entry.
- When a learning is backported to the canonical template, update the catalog metadata:
  - `backported: true`
  - `templateRef: <commit-sha or PR reference>`
